    <h1>First Assignment</h1>
    <hr>
    <h2>About &lt;b&gt; tag </h2>
    <p>The HTML tag is used to make text bold. It doesn't carry any semantic meaning on its own; it's just a
        presentational element.<b> When you enclose text within and tags, the text becomes visually bold on the
            webpage</b> </p>


    <h2>About &lt;i&gt; </h2>
    <p><i>The tag defines a part of text in an alternate voice or mood. The content inside is typically displayed in
            italic.</i></p>

    <h2>About &lt;u&gt;</h2>
    <p><u>The content inside is typically displayed with an underline.</u></p>
    <h2>About &lt;select&gt; tag</h2>
    <label for="select"></label>
    <select name="select" >
        <optgroup label="front end">
            <option value="html">html</option>
            <option value="css">css</option>
        </optgroup>
    </select>
<p>The  element is used to create a drop-down list. The element is most often used in a form, to collect user input. The name attribute is needed to reference the form data after the form is submitted (if you omit the name attribute, no data from the drop-down list will be submitted).</p>
<h2>About &lt;button&gt; tag</h2>
<p>The HTML element is an interactive element activated by a user with a mouse, keyboard, finger, voice command, or other assistive technology. Once activated, it then performs an action, such as submitting a form or opening a dialog.</p>
<button  > button </button>

<h2>About &lt;hr&gt; tag</h2>
<p>  By the use of this tag we can add a horizontal line to our html Document</p>
<hr>
<h2>Abour &lt;br&gt; tag</h2>
<p>By use of this tag we can add an extra blank line to our html page/content</p>




